Key Match Events: The Timberwolves rallied from a 13-point deficit to win the game.
Two Edwards 3s gave the Wolves a 113-106 advantage and forced the Bulls to call a timeout.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Minnesota struggled at the start of the game, but its stars got hot at the right time.
Chicago went 10 for 17 from 3-point range in the first half, but they were 5 of 19 from deep in the second half.
Others: Mike Conley had 14 points and 11 assists for the Timberwolves.
Nikola Vucevic scored 25 points for the Bulls on 11-for-15 shooting.
Julius Randle had 22 points and 10 rebounds for the Timberwolves, and Rudy Gobert finished with 21 points and nine boards.
